==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: analgesic
<hw>an`al*ge"sic</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧n`⟦acr⟧l*j⟦emac⟧"z⟦icr⟧k)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <grk>'analghsi`a</grk>; <grk>'an</grk>
priv. + <grk>'a`lghsis</grk> sense of pain.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld>
<def>a medication which serves to reduce the sensibility to pain without
loss of consciousness. Aspirin and acetaminophen (paracetamol, trade
name Tylenol) are commonly used non-prescription
<ex>analgesics</ex>.</def> <au>AS</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

